## Real-World Scenarios

### Scenario 1: Small Startup
**Requirements**: $500/month budget, 1 data engineer, quick start

**Databricks**:
- ✅ 5-minute setup
- ✅ All features integrated
- ✅ $150-300/month (Community + Trial)
- ❌ Vendor dependency

**AWS Native**:
- ✅ More control
- ✅ Pay-as-you-go
- ❌ 2-4 weeks setup (EMR, Glue, Athena, Airflow)
- ❌ $100-200/month (but 1 engineer's time costly)

**Recommendation**: 🏆 **Databricks** (faster time-to-value)

---

### Scenario 2: Enterprise with AWS Commitment
**Requirements**: $50K/month budget, 5 data engineers, AWS-only, existing AWS expertise

**Databricks**:
- ✅ Unified platform
- ✅ Advanced features (Unity, Photon)
- ❌ New platform to learn
- ❌ $10K-20K/month Databricks cost

**AWS Native**:
- ✅ Leverage existing AWS knowledge
- ✅ More flexibility
- ✅ No additional vendor
- ❌ Complex architecture (10+ services)
- ❌ Requires dedicated team
- ❌ $15K-30K/month (EMR, Redshift, MWAA, etc.)

**Recommendation**: 🏆 **Databricks** (unless strong AWS commitment or existing EMR expertise)

---

### Scenario 3: Multi-Cloud Strategy
**Requirements**: AWS + Azure, unified governance, 10 data engineers

**Databricks**:
- ✅ Same platform on AWS + Azure + GCP
- ✅ Unity Catalog across clouds
- ✅ Centralized governance
- ✅ Single training/expertise

**AWS Native**:
- ❌ AWS-only (need separate Azure solution)
- ❌ Different tools: Synapse Analytics (Azure), BigQuery (GCP)
- ❌ Fragmented governance

**Recommendation**: 🏆 **Databricks** (no other choice for multi-cloud)

