## Cost Comparison (Medium Workload)

### Databricks Monthly Cost
```
Compute (Jobs):    $3,000 (200 hours × $15/hr)
Storage (Delta):   $100 (5TB × $0.02/GB)
SQL Warehouse:     $500 (50 hours × $10/hr)
Databricks Fee:    $2,000 (DBUs)
-------------------------
Total:             $5,600/month
```

### AWS Native Monthly Cost
```
EMR Compute:       $2,500 (200 hours × $12.50/hr)
Redshift:          $2,000 (730 hours × $2.74/hr)
Athena:            $800 (160TB scanned × $5/TB)
MWAA:              $360 (730 hours × $0.49/hr)
Storage (S3):      $100 (5TB)
Glue Catalog:      $50
-------------------------
Total:             $5,810/month
```

**Analysis**: Similar cost, but Databricks includes:
- Faster queries (Photon)
- Integrated governance (Unity)
- Easier maintenance (unified platform)

